# JobbPiloten Environment Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values. NEVER commit .env
# or any of its variants (.env.local, .env.production, etc.) to git.
# See .gitignore for the ignore rules.
#
# SENTINEL FORMAT: every value below is the placeholder `__YOUR_*__`
# (no vendor prefix like `sk_test_` or `gsk_` â€” drop your real value
# over the ENTIRE placeholder). The double-underscore convention
# keeps the placeholder grep + machine-readable: a future
# `sed s/__YOUR_.*__//g` on this file strips them safely.

# ===== PRIVATE (server-only â€” NEVER prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_) =====
# These values must NOT ship to the client bundle. Read only on the
# server (Next.js route handlers, lib/groq.js, lib/auth.js). If you
# accidentally rename one to NEXT_PUBLIC_*, the build still succeeds
# but the secret becomes publicly visible to every visitor.

# MongoDB Atlas (or self-hosted) connection string.
MONGO_URL=mongodb+srv://__YOUR_DB_USER__:__YOUR_DB_PASSWORD__@__YOUR_CLUSTER__.mongodb.net/__YOUR_DB_NAME__?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# MongoDB database name.
DB_NAME=jobbpiloten

# --- LLM provider keys (intentionally OMITTED from this template) ---
# lib/groq.js's pickProvider() walks `LLM_KEY_NAMES` (at module
# scope) and uses `process.env[first-populated-name]` as the
# active API key. The 4 priority slots are:
#   GROQ_API_KEY       - canonical soft-launch provider
#   OPENAI_API_KEY     - direct OpenAI access
#   EMERGENT_LLM_KEY   - Emergent proxy (see comment block in lib/groq.js)
#   OPENROUTER_API_KEY - multi-provider router
# IMPORTANT: although pickProvider() walks the table, each
# provider branch in lib/groq.js is currently COMMENTED OUT â€”
# none of the 4 keys actually consume env values today. Adding
# a populated key would activate the walker, but the matching
# OpenAI-client branch in lib/groq.js has no working code path,
# so LLM calls would silently fall back to no-AI templates.
# To enable ONE provider, add ONE of these lines to your real
# .env AFTER uncommenting the matching branch in lib/groq.js.
# (Use the file's standard `__YOUR_*__` value-side sentinel
# convention; vendor prefixes are real but you only need to copy
# the LHS env var name and replace the entire RHS value.)
#   GROQ_API_KEY=__YOUR_ACTUAL_GROQ_KEY__
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=__YOUR_ACTUAL_OPENAI_KEY__
#   EMERGENT_LLM_KEY=__YOUR_ACTUAL_EMERGENT_KEY__
#   OPENROUTER_API_KEY=__YOUR_ACTUAL_OPENROUTER_KEY__
# (Do NOT add these placeholder lines here â€” keep all 4 keys absent.)
#
# CROSS-REFERENCE: EMERGENT_MODEL (below) is the actually-active
# runtime read today. EMERGENT_LLM_KEY only starts mattering once
# the corresponding provider branch in lib/groq.js is uncommented.

# --- LLM model override (lib/groq.js ACTIVE runtime reads) ---
# Both keys below are safe to set: they're read at runtime with
# hardcoded fallbacks, so an unset value uses the default model.
# Overriding here lets a maintainer switch models without code
# deploy (e.g. for cost / latency tuning during soft-launch).
#
# (Note: EMERGENT_MODEL is the actually-active runtime read. The
# EMERGENT_LLM_KEY branch in lib/groq.js is commented out — see the
# provider-key comment block ABOVE for the activation chain.)
EMERGENT_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
OPENROUTER_MODEL=anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet

# Clerk server-side secret (https://dashboard.clerk.com).
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=__YOUR_CLERK_SECRET_KEY__

# Stripe server-side secret (https://dashboard.stripe.com) â€” only if payments wired up.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=__YOUR_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY__

# Web Push VAPID private key â€” generate via `web-push generate-vapid-keys`.
VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=__YOUR_VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY__

# ===== PUBLIC (inlined at build time by Next.js â€” safe in client bundle) =====
# Next.js inlines any `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` env var into the JavaScript
# bundle at build time. The values are visible to every visitor â€”
# only put things here that are safe to expose (publishable keys,
# public URLs).

# Public base URL of the deployed app. Dev default is localhost:3000;
# production must point at https://jobbpiloten.se.
NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Clerk publishable key (safe to expose).
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=__YOUR_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY__

# Stripe publishable key (safe to expose) â€” only if payments wired up.
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=__YOUR_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY__

# Web Push VAPID public key (safe to expose) â€” sent to the browser so
# it can subscribe to push notifications.
NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=__YOUR_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY__

# ===== Clerk key rotation procedure (2026-07-21 / Round-79 followup) =====
# If your dev or prod deployment is stuck on demo mode (the
# Round-78 cascade: every route returns HTTP 500 with the cryptic
# `missing required error components, refreshing...` body), the most
# likely cause is a stale Clerk publishable key. The known-broken
# pre-fix key (`pk_test_ZXRlcm5hbC1waWthLTY0...` -> `eternal-pika-64`)
# is now blocklisted in lib/clerk-config.js -- leave it in .env and
# the app will silently fall back to demo mode (you will see it on the
# dashboard's "Inte ansluten" pill), but production traffic will not
# 500.
#
# To rotate to a FRESH Clerk instance (required for production):
#   1. Sign in to https://dashboard.clerk.com with the JobbPiloten
#      owner account.
#   2. Create a NEW Clerk application (or reuse an existing one for
#      the jobbpiloten.se domain).
#   3. From the API Keys tab, copy:
#        a. NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (the `pk_test_...` or
#           `pk_live_...` form -- safe to expose).
#        b. CLERK_SECRET_KEY (the `sk_test_...` or `sk_live_...` form
#           -- NEVER expose, server-only).
#   4. In Clerk's dashboard, add `localhost:3000` and
#      `https://jobbpiloten.se` to the Allowed Origins list
#      (otherwise the auth handshake postMessage is rejected).
#   5. Paste the keys over the `__YOUR_*__` placeholders in your
#      local .env (the .env template -- this file -- stays unchanged).
#   6. Restart `yarn dev`. The dashboard's "Ansluten -- profil redo"
#      pill confirms the new keys are accepted.
#
# After a successful rotation, remove the obsolete
# `pk_test_ZXRlcm5hbC1waWthLTY0` prefix from
# `KNOWN_BROKEN_CLERK_KEY_PREFIXES` in lib/clerk-config.js so the
# blocklist does not silently reject a legitimate key in some future
# scenario. The list is intentionally scan-friendly for that reason.
#
# If you DO NOT need Clerk for a soft-launch dev test, leave both
# keys as `__YOUR_*__` placeholders -- lib/clerk-config.js sees
# `key.includes('xxx')` as already invalid and falls back to demo
# mode without any 500.
